"# Alex Smith
Sydney, NSW, Australia · alex.smith@example.com · +61 400 000 000 · https://linkedin.com/in/alex-smith-dev · https://github.com/alexsmith

## Summary

Senior full-stack engineer with 8+ years expertise in TypeScript, React, and AWS. Built payment systems at scale and led platform migrations for fintech clients.

## Experience

### Acme Fintech Pty Ltd
**Senior Software Engineer** · Mar 2021 – Present
*Sydney, NSW · hybrid*

- Built internal developer portal using React and TypeScript, used daily by 120 engineers
- Architected event-driven payment processing pipeline handling 50k TPS using Kafka and Node.js, reducing latency by 40%
- Mentored 4 junior engineers; introduced ADR process adopted across 3 teams
- Led migration of monolith to microservices, cutting deployment time from 2 hours to 8 minutes via GitHub Actions + ECS

### StartupXYZ
**Software Engineer** · June 2018 – Feb 2021
*Sydney, NSW · onsite*

- Reduced API p99 latency from 800 ms to 120 ms by introducing a Redis caching layer
- Built real-time analytics dashboard using React, D3.js, and WebSocket, serving 200+ enterprise clients
- Delivered GDPR compliance features end-to-end within 6-week regulatory deadline

## Skills

**Languages:** TypeScript, Python
**Frameworks:** React, Node.js
**Tools:** AWS, PostgreSQL, Kafka, Terraform, Redis, Docker

## Education

### University of New South Wales
**Bachelor of Engineering (Honours), Software Engineering** · Feb 2014 – Nov 2018
*First Class Honours*
GPA: 6.5

## Certifications

- **AWS Certified Solutions Architect – Associate** — Amazon Web Services · May 2022 (expires May 2025)

## Projects

### OpenTraceQL — [https://opentraceql.dev](https://opentraceql.dev)
*TypeScript, Node.js*
Open-source query language for distributed trace analysis, used by 300+ developers
- 300+ GitHub stars"
